<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,522,1007,1034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[269,372,1008,1034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">holotype</typeStatus>
description.
</emphasis>
Length of forewing: 
<quantity box="[771,856,1008,1034]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
. Eye smooth. Antenna dark brown above and pale greyish brown below, with club mostly blackish brown, and with shaft obscurely segmented by pale scales. Body above black, clad with long yellowish setae, below densely clad with yellow scales. Frons and palpi clad with yellow scales, mixed with pale yellow and grayish setae. Legs clad with yellow scales, mixed with yellow setae. Both wings same shaped as in other two subspecies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Wing-pattern generally as in other two subspecies. Ciliae pale yellow on both wings both sides, mixed sparsely with pink ones.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" box="[199,1257,1259,1286]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Male genitalia as in other two subspecies, not separable from most of the other 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1257,1259,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1088,1161,1259,1285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Colias</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,554,1295,1322]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Description of male 
<typeStatus box="[436,554,1296,1322]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">paratypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Length of forewing: 
<quantity box="[796,918,1295,1322]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="24.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="23.0">23– 26mm</quantity>
, mostly 
<quantity box="[1010,1133,1295,1322]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="24.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="24.0">24– 25mm</quantity>
. Ground color of wings upper side pale yellow, occasionally whitish (Specimen P2). Individual variations mainly found in marginal markings on forewing upper side and postdiscal fasciae on both wings upper side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,579,1403,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Description of female 
<typeStatus box="[461,579,1404,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">paratypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Length of forewing: 
<quantity box="[825,945,1403,1430]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="24.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="23.0">23- 26mm</quantity>
. Upper side ground color more whitish than in males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1476,1502]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the narrower marginal markings on forewing upper side of the new subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1547,1573]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This new subspecies can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[869,1046,1547,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[920,1046,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[1102,1242,1548,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1153,1242,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: 1) forewing upper side marginal markings, especially the one on vein 5, constantly narrower than in other subspecies; 2) size generally much larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[946,1123,1619,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[997,1123,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, slightly larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[151,240,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 3) forewing upper side postdiscal fasciae less developed than in other subspecies, duller and narrower, often more or less interrupted by veins; 4) hindwing upper side postdiscal fasciae usually obsolete (invariably well developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[302,441,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[352,441,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 5) hindwing upper side discal area paler than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[1003,1142,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1053,1142,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not so black-dusted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="463" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,863,2042]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="463" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1764,1790]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Remarks</emphasis>
. Only two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[585,790,1763,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasibulus">
<emphasis box="[585,790,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Colias thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were considered as valid in Grieshuber et al’s (2012) revision and 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[252,478,1799,1826]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber’s (2014)</bibRefCitation>
Guide book: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[631,807,1799,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[681,807,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from Ladakh Range (Kardung La and Chonging Valley, N. or NW. of Kardung La- TL of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[610,736,1835,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasibulus">
<emphasis box="[610,736,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Zanskar Range (Taglang La - TL of 
<emphasis box="[1166,1308,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">zanskarensis</emphasis>
; Nimaling; vicinity of Morari Lake), E. Karakorum Range (Sasser La, Shimshin Jilga - Cretschmar, [1935]), W. 
<collectingRegion box="[1283,1341,1871,1897]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(Zhabu, Rebang, Ritu - 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, C. - L." box="[327,440,1908,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref15770" refString="Lee, C. - L. (1982) Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera. In: Huang, F. - S. (Ed.), Insects of Xizang, Vol. 2. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 127 - 154." type="book" year="1982">Lee, 1982</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, C. - S." box="[479,594,1908,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref16533" refString="Wu, C. - S. (2010) Fauna Sinica. Insecta Vol. 52. Lepidoptera Pieridae. Science Press, Beijing, 416 pp., 16 pls. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2010">Wu, 2010</bibRefCitation>
; Yanhu, Gejie - 
<bibRefCitation author="Verhulst, J." box="[779,947,1907,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref16453" refString="Verhulst, J. (2001) Les Colias du Globe. Monograph of the genus Colias. Plates. Goecke &amp; Evers, Kelterns, 45 pp., 183 pls. [in French]" type="book" year="2001">Verhulst, 2001</bibRefCitation>
; W. of Paryang - 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[1149,1346,1907,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber, 2014</bibRefCitation>
) and C. 
<collectingRegion box="[151,209,1943,1969]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(S. of Namco Lake - 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoshiai, A." box="[458,620,1943,1970]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" pagination="8 - 10" refId="ref15351" refString="Hoshiai, A. (1996) Notes of Colias from China and surrounding area (1). In: Koiwaya, S. (Ed.), Studies of Chinese Butterflies. Vol. 3. S. Koiwaya, Tokyo, pp. 211 - 217, pls. 8 - 10. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="1996">Hoshiai, 1996</bibRefCitation>
); and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[689,829,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[740,829,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known only from Yushu, SE. 
<collectingRegion box="[1172,1266,1943,1969]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoshiai" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="zanskarensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">C. thrasibulus zanskarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retained by 
<bibRefCitation author="Verhulst, J." box="[487,663,1979,2006]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref16453" refString="Verhulst, J. (2001) Les Colias du Globe. Monograph of the genus Colias. Plates. Goecke &amp; Evers, Kelterns, 45 pp., 183 pls. [in French]" type="book" year="2001">Verhulst (2001)</bibRefCitation>
as good subspecies for the populations from Zanskar Range and W. 
<collectingRegion box="[151,212,2015,2041]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Tibet</collectingRegion>
, but was regarded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J. &amp; Worthy, R. &amp; Lamas, G." box="[468,745,2015,2042]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refId="ref15180" refString="Grieshuber, J., Worthy, R. &amp; Lamas, G. (2012) The genus Colias Fabricius, 1807. Jan Haugum's annotated catalogue of the Old World Colias. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice, 438 pp." type="book" year="2012">
Grieshuber 
<emphasis box="[602,661,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
as synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[931,1109,2015,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[983,1109,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “it is within the range of variation of nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[462,623,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasibulus">
<emphasis box="[462,623,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">C. thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. It is difficult to sort the population from S. of Namco, C. 
<collectingRegion box="[1314,1375,151,177]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Tibet</collectingRegion>
, as it is intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[433,612,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[486,612,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[673,815,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[726,815,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in distribution and wing-characters. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[1242,1389,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
Ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1300,1389,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only slight difference from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="thrasibulus Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[464,641,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="thrasibulus">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[515,641,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the darker discal area on hindwing upper side, however, the newly collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[415,555,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[466,555,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Yushu confirm that this slight difference is rather constant. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kocman" authorityYear="2003" box="[200,339,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="thrasibulus" subSpecies="fasciata">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[250,339,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only the end of a cline of nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[827,985,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasibulus">
<emphasis box="[827,985,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">C. thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the other hand, the new subspecies, 
<emphasis box="[151,355,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">angustomarginata</emphasis>
appears to produce a entirely different phenotype with large size and obsolete black markings and suffusion on the wings upper side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
The zoogeographical pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1910" box="[570,779,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thrasibulus">
<emphasis box="[570,779,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Colias thrasibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recalls that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Esper, 1783)" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1783" box="[958,1351,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Hipparchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autonoe">
<emphasis box="[958,1186,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Hipparchia autonoe</emphasis>
(Esper, 1783)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nymphalidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1833" box="[262,352,439,466]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Satyrini">Satyrini</taxonomicName>
) in Tibetan plateau: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1783" box="[587,713,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Hipparchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autonoe">
<emphasis box="[587,713,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">H. autonoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
changes a little from W. 
<collectingRegion box="[1000,1058,439,465]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Markhasiov, 2021" authorityName="Markhasiov" authorityYear="2021" box="[1075,1428,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="mabcha">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1127,1216,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">mabcha</emphasis>
Markhasiov, 2021
</taxonomicName>
) to Yushu, SE. 
<collectingRegion box="[310,400,475,501]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Lang, 2019" authorityName="Lang" authorityYear="2019" box="[417,694,475,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="songkui">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[467,554,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">songkui</emphasis>
Lang, 2019
</taxonomicName>
), but turns to be much brighter at Dulan-Balong areas, C. 
<collectingRegion box="[1346,1436,475,501]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Sbordoni, Bozano &amp; Cesaroni, 2018" authorityName="Sbordoni, Bozano &amp; Cesaroni" authorityYear="2018" box="[160,721,511,537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="arcellae">
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[210,301,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">arcellae</emphasis>
Sbordoni, Bozano &amp; Cesaroni, 2018
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
